‎躺在柳树旁哭泣
and weep beside the tree.

00:01:41.200 --> 00:01:43.500
‎唱着 "哦 伤心的柳树"
Singin', "O willow waly"

00:01:48.870 --> 00:01:50.750
‎柳树也跟着我流泪
by the tree that weeps with me.

00:01:54.410 --> 00:01:57.290
‎唱着 "哦 伤心的柳树"
Singing, "O willow waly"

00:02:02.830 --> 00:02:04.790
‎直到爱人回到我身旁
till my lover return to me.

00:02:24.450 --> 00:02:26.830
‎请大家听我说 好吗
Can I have your attention, please?

00:02:27.330 --> 00:02:30.450
‎你们马上就要用餐 但是...
You'll get to your meals momentarily, but first...

00:02:31.370 --> 00:02:33.580
‎新娘请我先说几句
the bride has asked me to speak.

00:02:33.700 --> 00:02:35.000
‎我以为她在开玩笑
I thought she was joking!

00:02:35.080 --> 00:02:37.750
‎你为什么要给自己的婚礼
Why invite such catastrophe

00:02:37.830 --> 00:02:39.250
‎找这样的麻烦
upon your own wedding?

00:02:39.330 --> 00:02:41.910
‎不过她解释说
But, as she explained,

00:02:42.120 --> 00:02:44.120
‎"不 才不是呢 不是婚礼
"No, heavens, no. Not the wedding,

00:02:44.200 --> 00:02:45.580
‎是练习餐"
the practice meal."

00:02:45.660 --> 00:02:48.250
‎拜托 这是预演晚宴
The rehearsal dinner, for God's sakes!

00:02:48.330 --> 00:02:50.980
‎身为略有醉意
I must claim my right as a slightly drunk,

00:02:50.980 --> 00:02:52.540
时差还没倒过来的英国人
completely jet-lagged Englishman

00:02:52.620 --> 00:02:54.910
‎我要声明 我说的都是真心话
to well and truly speak my mind.

00:02:55.000 --> 00:02:56.790
‎因为我想提醒你们大家
Because I want to warn you all,

00:02:56.870 --> 00:02:59.660
‎你们年轻人完全不知道
you young people have absolutely no idea

00:02:59.750 --> 00:03:02.160
‎你们让自己陷入了什么境地
what you are letting yourselves in for.

00:03:08.450 --> 00:03:09.950
‎有个可怕的统计数据
Here's a horrifying statistic.

00:03:10.040 --> 00:03:12.750
‎你们知道现在几乎有一半的婚姻
Did you know that almost half of marriages these days

00:03:12.830 --> 00:03:15.000
‎没有以离婚告终吗
do not end up in divorce?

00:03:16.830 --> 00:03:20.010
‎也就是说 你们俩很有可能
That means there's a strong probability that you two

00:03:20.010 --> 00:03:21.750
看着对方死去
get to watch each other die.

00:03:22.200 --> 00:03:24.450
‎这是人们想要的结果
And that's the preferred outcome.

00:03:24.830 --> 00:03:27.160
‎真正爱另一个人
To truly love another person

00:03:27.620 --> 00:03:30.950
‎就是要接受 爱之深切
is to accept that the work of loving them

00:03:31.580 --> 00:03:33.790
‎失去后痛也值得
is worth the pain of losing them.

00:03:34.750 --> 00:03:35.750
‎就是这样
And that's it.

00:03:36.790 --> 00:03:37.790
‎仅此而已
That's all.

00:03:38.290 --> 00:03:40.950
‎如果你也像我一样害怕
And if that scares you as much as it scares me,

00:03:41.040 --> 00:03:42.160
‎那我会说"快跑"
then I say run.

00:03:42.250 --> 00:03:44.700
‎跑到巴厘岛的海滩上嗑药吧
Go off and do drugs on a beach in Bali.

00:03:44.790 --> 00:03:46.830
‎全身心投入到精神生活中
Devote yourself to a life of the mind. Run!

00:03:46.910 --> 00:03:48.440
‎快跑 趁你还能跑
Run while you still can.

00:03:48.440 --> 00:03:50.620
你还年轻 你身体强壮 这个世界...
You're young, you're strong. The world...

00:03:50.700 --> 00:03:51.790
‎不 我说真的 ‎
No, I'm serious,

00:03:51.870 --> 00:03:54.410
-我们其实不愿意住在这里  -她不愿意
- we actually refused to stay here. - She refused.

00:03:54.500 --> 00:03:56.980
‎我还以为非要住在这里
I didn't know staying here was even an option.

00:03:57.040 --> 00:03:58.720
‎城堡里有三个套房
There's three suites in the castle,

00:03:58.750 --> 00:04:00.930
-杰克想住在这里...  -就住一晚
- and Jack wanted to stay here... - Just one night.

00:04:00.950 --> 00:04:02.370
然后我们去度蜜月
before we left for the honeymoon.

00:04:02.450 --> 00:04:04.340
‎就在明天婚宴之后
Just tomorrow. Just after the reception,

00:04:04.340 --> 00:04:05.620
让我们跌跌撞撞地上楼
so we could just stumble upstairs.

00:04:06.040 --> 00:04:08.290
‎但我说 "不行 ‎听了那些故事后可不行"
But I said, "No way, not after those stories."

00:04:08.370 --> 00:04:10.450
‎等等 只是故事而已
Wait, just the stories?

00:04:10.540 --> 00:04:13.370
‎-你没看到她  ‎-不 天啊 我没看到她
- You didn't see her? - No! God no, I didn't see her.

00:04:13.450 --> 00:04:16.750
‎要是我看到死去的女人 ‎死去的修女在角落里哭泣
If I saw a dead woman, a dead nun, no less, crying in the corners,

00:04:17.200 --> 00:04:19.830
‎-我们不会在这里结婚  ‎-好了 只是故事而已
- we would not be getting married here. - Okay, it's just a story.

00:04:19.910 --> 00:04:23.540
‎这地方在40年代是个修道院 ‎有几十年的历史
This place used to be a convent for, like, a few decades in the '40s.

00:04:23.620 --> 00:04:24.860
‎这是销售套餐的内容
It's part of the sales package.

00:04:24.910 --> 00:04:27.580
‎他们讲这个鬼故事 ‎可能多收几百美元
They can charge a few hundred extra for the ghost story.

00:04:27.830 --> 00:04:31.790
‎听着 我喜欢精彩的鬼故事 ‎只是不想听了去睡觉
Look, I love a good ghost story, I just don't want to sleep in one.

00:04:31.870 --> 00:04:33.580
‎我们在爱尔兰度蜜月
We honeymooned in Ireland.

00:04:34.290 --> 00:04:36.200
‎他们不停地告诉我们要小心
They kept telling us to look out for Seamus,

00:04:36.290 --> 00:04:37.160
‎马房男孩谢默斯
the stable boy.

00:04:37.250 --> 00:04:39.000
‎谢默斯
Seamus.

00:04:39.080 --> 00:04:42.370
‎据说他的头被马踢碎了
They said his head was crushed in where a horse had kicked him.

00:04:42.450 --> 00:04:44.620
‎鬼故事中要是有小孩 就更吓人
Ghost stories are worse when there's a kid.

00:04:44.700 --> 00:04:47.370
‎加了点料 不是吗
Adds a little something, doesn't it?

00:04:47.500 --> 00:04:48.540
‎我有个故事
I have a story.

00:04:51.200 --> 00:04:52.200
‎好吧...
Well...

00:04:53.250 --> 00:04:54.660
‎这不是我的亲身经历
it isn't really my story.

00:04:55.250 --> 00:04:56.700
‎是我认识的一个人
It belongs to someone I knew.

00:04:57.950 --> 00:04:59.660
‎这个故事说来话长
And it's not exactly short.

00:05:00.450 --> 00:05:03.000
‎我们的时间似乎很充足...
Well, it seems we have time enough, and...

00:05:03.080 --> 00:05:04.080
‎葡萄酒也够喝
wine enough.

00:05:05.870 --> 00:05:06.870
‎干吗不讲呢
Why not?

00:05:17.000 --> 00:05:18.000
‎那好吧
All right, then.

00:05:18.870 --> 00:05:19.870
‎有个鬼故事
A ghost story.

00:05:22.000 --> 00:05:24.450
‎再说一次 这个故事不是我的
Again, this story isn't mine,

00:05:25.290 --> 00:05:28.620
‎但里面有各种各样的鬼魂
but it is full of ghosts of all sorts.

00:05:30.160 --> 00:05:32.370
‎要是一个小孩很吓人
And if a child gives the effect,

00:05:33.040 --> 00:05:34.950
‎让故事更惊心动魄...
another turn of the screw...

00:05:37.750 --> 00:05:38.950
‎那么两个小孩会如何
what do you say to two?

00:05:48.200 --> 00:05:51.450
‎这位孤单的年轻女子 ‎出于自愿当了老师
The teacher was, by choice, a solitary young woman.

00:05:51.950 --> 00:05:55.910
‎她忐忑不安地来到伦敦 当面应聘一则广告...
Come up to London in trepidation to answer in person an advertisement...

00:05:57.200 --> 00:05:59.160
亨利·温格雷夫爵士发布了‎这则广告
placed by one Lord Henry Wingrave

00:05:59.950 --> 00:06:01.790
‎为他年幼的侄子和侄女
regarding his young nephew and niece,

00:06:02.200 --> 00:06:03.830
‎招聘家庭教师
who were in need of an au pair.

00:06:04.120 --> 00:06:06.500
‎广告上说这是全职工作
A full-time position, it said. Live-in, at that,

00:06:07.200 --> 00:06:09.200
‎住在埃塞克斯 他古老的家族宅邸
in his old family home in Essex.

00:06:09.700 --> 00:06:10.910
‎一个不错的好地方
A great good place,

00:06:11.330 --> 00:06:12.450
‎在乡下与世隔绝
alone in the country.

00:06:30.700 --> 00:06:31.870
‎是克莱顿小姐吗
Miss Clayton, is it?

00:06:31.950 --> 00:06:34.040
‎叫我丹妮就行 你好
Call me Dani. Hi there.

00:06:34.120 --> 00:06:35.450
‎请坐吧
Please, have a seat.

00:06:39.080 --> 00:06:40.950
‎-你是老师吗  ‎-是的
- You're a teacher? - Yes.

00:06:41.870 --> 00:06:42.870
‎我当过老师
Or I was.

00:06:43.500 --> 00:06:44.500
‎教四年级
Fourth grade.

00:06:44.830 --> 00:06:45.870
‎在美国
In the States.

00:06:49.200 --> 00:06:50.370
‎来英国很久了吗
Been in England long?

00:06:51.120 --> 00:06:52.950
‎大概六个月
About six months.

00:06:53.040 --> 00:06:55.540
‎六个月 你在此期间...
Six months? During which time, you've...

00:06:56.660 --> 00:06:57.830
‎我已经...
Well, I've...

00:06:57.910 --> 00:07:00.030
相当钟情于伦敦
fallen quite in love with London.

00:07:01.040 --> 00:07:02.040
‎很好
God.

00:07:04.120 --> 00:07:05.370
‎茶还是咖啡
Tea? Coffee?

00:07:06.370 --> 00:07:09.540
‎不了 谢谢 我还不太懂得喝茶
No, thank you. Haven't quite mastered tea yet.

00:07:10.040 --> 00:07:11.790
‎我习惯用水壶泡茶
I'm used to it coming in a pitcher.

00:07:12.200 --> 00:07:13.200
‎放满冰块...
Full of ice cubes...

00:07:14.540 --> 00:07:15.870
‎还有柠檬角
and lemon wedges, and...

00:07:16.540 --> 00:07:18.540
‎这里的茶完全不一样
Well, it's a whole different thing here.

00:07:19.750 --> 00:07:21.830
‎是的 没错
Yes, it is.

00:07:24.000 --> 00:07:27.620
‎你以前没有做家庭教师的经验
You've no previous experience as an au pair.

00:07:28.700 --> 00:07:29.700
‎我...
Well, I...

00:07:30.250 --> 00:07:33.160
‎我教孩子的经验很丰富 ‎温格雷夫先生
I've quite a bit of experience with children, Mr. Wingrave.

00:07:33.250 --> 00:07:37.200
‎那是在教室 可这是全职住家工作
In a classroom, but this is a full-time, live-in position.

00:07:37.290 --> 00:07:38.700
‎我知道 所以我才
I know, that's actually why

00:07:38.790 --> 00:07:41.120
-回复广告  -孩子们很可爱
- I responded to the ad. - The children are wonderful.

00:07:41.200 --> 00:07:43.540
‎我的侄女和侄子真的很出色
Exceptional, really, my niece and my nephew.

00:07:43.620 --> 00:07:45.910
‎像我说的那样 出色的孩子
Exceptional children, as I said.

00:07:46.790 --> 00:07:49.450
‎但两个孩子都很难管
But challenging, both.

00:07:49.540 --> 00:07:53.700
‎我侄子迈尔斯 ‎提前从寄宿学校回家了
Miles, my nephew, is back home from boarding school early.

00:07:54.330 --> 00:07:55.580
‎恐怕他比以往更需要
He needs structure,

00:07:55.660 --> 00:07:57.500
‎约束和纪律
discipline more than ever, I fear.

00:07:59.700 --> 00:08:01.540
‎我能问一下 他为什么被送回家吗
Well, can I ask why he was sent home?

00:08:01.870 --> 00:08:04.430
‎-春季学期不该结束...  ‎-你要辅导他的功课
- Spring session shouldn't end... - You'd be expected to tutor him

00:08:04.450 --> 00:08:05.910
‎让他不要成绩落后
so he doesn't fall behind.

00:08:06.120 --> 00:08:10.330
‎你的课堂经验 ‎其实会在这方面派上用场
In that respect, your classroom experience may actually be of use.

00:08:10.910 --> 00:08:12.450
‎我的侄女弗洛拉
The same with Flora,

00:08:12.540 --> 00:08:13.580
‎也是如此
my niece.

00:08:14.250 --> 00:08:15.580
‎你也要辅导她
You'd tutor her as well.

00:08:15.910 --> 00:08:19.450
‎你的广告提到这份工作在乡间
Your ad mentioned the position was in the countryside?

00:08:19.910 --> 00:08:21.000
‎在布莱
In Bly,

00:08:21.790 --> 00:08:23.410
‎我家族的乡间庄园
my family's country house.

00:08:24.870 --> 00:08:26.870
‎孩子们习惯了布莱 他们...
The children are used to Bly, they...

00:08:27.540 --> 00:08:30.830
‎跟着父母在那里度过暑假和假日
spent summers and holidays there with their parents,

00:08:31.580 --> 00:08:32.660
‎在父母去世前
before they passed.

00:08:33.450 --> 00:08:35.290
‎这座庄园是个不错的好地方
It's a great good place, the manor.

00:08:35.910 --> 00:08:37.750
‎庄园里几乎没有其他人
There are few others on the grounds.

00:08:37.830 --> 00:08:41.000
‎厨师 园丁都住在镇上
A cook, groundskeeper. They stay in town.

00:08:41.950 --> 00:08:44.370
‎有位管家住在家里 但孩子们...
There is a live-in housekeeper, but the children...

00:08:44.750 --> 00:08:47.950
‎将由你负责 你一个人负责
would be your responsibility and yours alone.

00:08:48.500 --> 00:08:51.750
‎除非有急事 否则不要给我打电话
Don't call on me unless it's an emergency.

00:08:51.830 --> 00:08:53.370
‎我特别忙
I'm extraordinarily busy.

00:08:54.120 --> 00:08:55.290
‎我懂了
I understand.

00:08:56.540 --> 00:08:57.370
‎你知道
You know,

00:08:57.540 --> 00:09:00.620
‎在我的学校 我有个更特别的任务
one of my more unique assignments at my school

00:09:00.870 --> 00:09:03.330
是要专门照顾一些最需要帮助的孩子
was specific to some of our highest-need children,

00:09:03.410 --> 00:09:06.700
‎-他们中又一个失去了...  ‎-有什么隐情
- one of whom had actually lost their par... - What's the catch?

00:09:08.700 --> 00:09:09.700
‎你说什么
I'm sorry?

00:09:10.200 --> 00:09:11.830
‎隐情 你多大了
The catch. You're what?

00:09:13.200 --> 00:09:14.080
‎30岁
Thirty?

00:09:14.160 --> 00:09:15.330
‎25岁
Mid-twenties?

00:09:16.330 --> 00:09:17.330
‎我想知道...
I wonder...

00:09:17.910 --> 00:09:19.120
‎有什么隐情
What's the catch?

00:09:19.450 --> 00:09:22.040
‎你比应聘这类工作的大多数人都年轻
You're younger than most who'd apply for this sort of thing.

00:09:22.120 --> 00:09:25.120
‎是什么让你这个年纪的女人
What makes a woman of your age

00:09:25.200 --> 00:09:28.950
‎愿意放弃自己的生活 ‎去照顾别人的孩子
want to give up her life to take care of someone else's children?

00:09:29.410 --> 00:09:31.120
‎放弃美国的生活
A life in America, at that.

00:09:31.580 --> 00:09:32.790
‎还是全职工作
Full-time as well.

00:09:34.540 --> 00:09:37.950
‎老实说 我觉得很奇怪
It seems odd... to me, to be frank.

00:09:41.950 --> 00:09:43.250
‎我也觉得很奇怪
It seems odd to me too.

00:09:44.580 --> 00:09:45.750
‎我是说广告
The listing, I mean.

00:09:47.540 --> 00:09:49.620
‎全职工作 住在美丽的乡村庄园
A full-time position in a beautiful country manor

00:09:49.700 --> 00:09:51.250
‎照顾两个出色的孩子
to two exceptional children.

00:09:52.080 --> 00:09:53.750
‎但我六个月前看过你的广告
But I saw your ad six months ago.

00:09:54.620 --> 00:09:56.200
‎我刚到伦敦的时候
When I first arrived in London.

00:09:56.370 --> 00:09:58.660
‎此后我每个月都会看到
And I have seen it every month since.

00:10:01.080 --> 00:10:03.000
‎我觉得这个工作很容易招到人
Seems to me an easy position to fill.

00:10:05.000 --> 00:10:06.660
‎至少像你描述的那样
At least as you've described.

00:10:09.080 --> 00:10:10.450
‎所以我想你说得对
So, I suppose you're right.

00:10:12.330 --> 00:10:13.450
‎有什么隐情
What is the catch?

00:10:14.580 --> 00:10:16.040
‎这确实是个问题
That really is the question.

00:10:22.200 --> 00:10:23.200
‎谢谢
Thank you.

